# Supabase — used by the Pipeline CSV importer (app/api/pipeline/upload).
# SERVER-SIDE ONLY. The service role key bypasses Row Level Security, so it must
# never be exposed to the browser (do NOT prefix it with NEXT_PUBLIC_).
#
# Find these in: Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values, then restart `next dev`.
#
# If these are left unset, the Pipeline tool runs in DEMO mode: it parses the CSV
# and animates the flow but simulates the write instead of hitting Supabase.

# This is a TEMPLATE. Never paste real keys here — only into .env.local (gitignored).
SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# ── Send Campaigns (Automation) — Pipeline → Send Campaigns tab ──
# The n8n webhook that delivers the outreach emails. The tab POSTs the rendered,
# per-lead messages here ({ campaign, messages: [{ to, subject, html, leadId }] }).
# Point it at a Webhook-trigger node fronting the "Send a message" Gmail node in
# references/Leadgen Automation.json. If unset, sends run in DEMO mode (simulated,
# nothing delivered) — exactly like the importer without Supabase creds.
# N8N_CAMPAIGN_WEBHOOK_URL=https://your-n8n.example.com/webhook/apmg-campaign

# Public base URL the tracked CTA links point at, e.g. /t/<lead>?c=<campaign>
# (see app/t/[id]/route.ts). Optional — defaults to the request origin. Set this
# to your deployed domain so links in emails resolve correctly. Safe to expose
# (NEXT_PUBLIC_), it's only a hostname.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TRACK_BASE=https://apmg-app.vercel.app
